   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>Haughton, a weaver in <placeName>Chinley End, Derbyshire</placeName>, became one
                  of <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s early <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preachers</seg>, mentioned as a special Assistant in
                     <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName> in <date when="1746">1746</date>. He went to
                     <placeName>Ireland</placeName> with <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> in <date when="1747">1747</date>, and spent the remainder of his ministry there. In <date when="1755">1755</date> he is listed as a Methodist local preacher in
                     <placeName>Dublin</placeName>. In <date when="1759">1759</date> he secured
                  episcopal ordination from the Bishop of Derry (<persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers0105.xml"/>William Barnard</persName>), and appointment
                  as rector of <placeName>Kilrea, Londonderry</placeName>, where he 'cordially
                  received' <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> in
                     <date when="1778">1778</date>. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>,
                  202.</p>
            
         
